-- Rosneft, Sberbank, Severstal May Be Active: Russian Equity Market Preview
-- Denis Maternovsky
-- 2010-07-01T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/rosneft-sberbank-severstal-may-be-active-russian-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  
 Russia’s ruble-based  Micex Index  fell for a second day,
declining 1.1 percent to 1,309.31 in Moscow. The dollar-
denominated  RTS Index  retreated 1.2 percent to 1,339.35.  
 OAO Rosneft : (ROSN RX) and  OAO Lukoil  (LKOH RX): Crude oil
for August delivery dropped 1.7 percent to $74.63 a barrel,
capping the first quarterly decline since 2008, as a U.S.
government report showed that gasoline stockpiles increased for
the first time in eight weeks. Shares of Rosneft, Russia’s
biggest oil company, fell 1 percent to 192.79 rubles, the lowest
level since August 2009. Lukoil shares declined 1.6 percent to
1,621.56 rubles.  
 OAO Sberbank  (SBER03 RX) priced $1 billion of five-year
bonds to yield 345 basis points more than the benchmark mid-swap
rate, the lender’s first international debt sale in two years.
Bank shares fell 1.1 percent to 76.68 rubles.  
 OAO Severstal  (CHMF RX) completed the sale of Lucchini SpA
to a company controlled by  Alexey Mordashov , the company said in
a regulatory filing after trading in Moscow closed. Russia’s
biggest steelmaker fell 2.2 percent to 308.09 rubles.  
